    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our lineup leans heavily into exploiting favorable matchups against secondary pitching, with **Tyler Freeman** (72.83) and **Gleyber Torres** (67.46) serving as our strongest plays. **Tyler Freeman** benefits from a potent combination of a hitter-friendly park and a +19% boost from opposing starter Walker Buehler\u2019s shaky xERA. Critically, we are also tracking the stolen base potential here; the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery significantly enhances **Tyler Freeman**'s profile in our pursuit of the league\u2019s scarcest category. Similarly, **Gleyber Torres** is poised for a high-efficiency outing against DL Hall, where the confluence of a +19% SP skill advantage and a +13% platoon boost makes him an essential start. We are also monitoring the wind in games involving **Taylor Ward**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, and **Daulton Varsho**, as projected wind-out conditions are providing a tangible lift to their base projections.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Matt Chapman**, who fell just shy of the lineup with a score of 46.10. While **Matt Chapman** is a reliable asset, the prohibitive matchup against Shohei Ohtani suppressed his SP skill modifier by 19%, ultimately making him the odd man out in favor of the higher-ceiling outcomes for **Gavin Sheets** and **Wenceel Perez**. We are currently carrying several \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Will Smith**, **Luis Arraez**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, and **Gavin Sheets**; should those confirmed orders shift downward, we may see further volatility in our daily efficiency scores. Owners should remain cautious of the volatility inherent in facing elite arms like Ohtani, which has tempered our expectations for **Luis Arraez** and **Geraldo Perdomo** despite their projected roles in the heart of the order.",
